<TITLE>Stephen Langlois</TITLE>

<PARAGRAPH>
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="1" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="plain_name" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="name" CASE="plain" TAG="plain_name" NEW="yes">Stephen Langlois</REFEX>
</REF>
 is a Chicago area chef and co-author of Prairie: Cuisine from the Heartland (with 
<REF ENTITY="1" MENTION="1" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="obj" PREDICTION="plain_name" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="1" REG08-TYPE="name" CASE="plain" TAG="plain_name" NEW="yes">Margaret Guthrie</REFEX>
</REF>
).
</PARAGRAPH>

<PARAGRAPH>
Currently executive chef of the Hyatt Lodge in Oak Brook, Illinois, 
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="2" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="plain_name_family" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="name" CASE="plain" TAG="plain_name_family" NEW="yes">Langlois</REFEX>
</REF>
 was one of the chefs defining Midwestern cuisine in the 20th century. As chef of the now-closed Prairie in Chicago from 1986 to 1997, 
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="3" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="nominative_pronoun_he" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" CASE="nominative" TAG="nominative_pronoun_he" NEW="yes">he</REFEX>
</REF>
 showcased strictly regional fare, even steering clear of ocean fish.
</PARAGRAPH>

<PARAGRAPH>
A graduate of the hospitality program at Triton College in River Grove, Illinois and the Culinary Institute of America in Hyde Park, New York, 
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="4" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="nominative_pronoun_he" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" CASE="nominative" TAG="nominative_pronoun_he" NEW="yes">he</REFEX>
</REF>
 also worked at the Chicago restaurants Cafe D'Artagnan and Maxim's and the Pulitzer Hotel in Amsterdam, Netherlands.
</PARAGRAPH>
